dcterms:creator: benshi.ai
dcterms:description: HealthSyn is an open-source synthetic data generator of user behavior for testing reinforcement learning algorithms in the context of mobile health interventions. It utilizes Markov processes to generate diverse user actions, with individual user behavioral patterns that can change in reaction to personalized interventions.
dcterms:title: HealthSyn

dcterms:creator: benshi.ai
dcterms:description: HealthKit is an open-source Software Developer Kit (SDK) for mobile health that tracks, labels, and organizes user logs in a data schema optimized for machine learning and intervention purposes. It tracks general in-app user behavior and additional events organized based on the type of content.
dcterms:title: HealthKit
